hadithEnglish:
It was narrated that Abu Kabshah Al-Anmari said:
&ldquo;The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: The likeness of this nation is that of four people: A man to whom Allah gives wealth and knowledge, so he acts according to his knowledge with regard to his wealth, spending it as it should be spent; a man to whom Allah gives knowledge, but he does not give him wealth, so he says: &ldquo;If I had been given (wealth) like this one, I would have done what (the first man) did.&rdquo; The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: They will be equal in reward. And a man to whom Allah gives wealth but does not give knowledge, so he squanders his wealth and spends it in inappropriate ways; and a man to whom Allah gives neither knowledge nor wealth, and he says: &ldquo;If I had (wealth) like this one, I would do what (the third man) did.&rdquo; The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: They are equal in their burden (of sin).&rdquo;

 A similar report (as above) was narrated from Ibn Abu Kabshah, from his father, from the Prophet (ﷺ).
